FBIS4-56907 "drlat091_b_94010" FBIS-LAT-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 Aruba Haiti AJEPOPOA Congratulates Senate on Decision AJEPOPOA Congratulates Senate on Decision FL1005215594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1700 GMT 10 May 94 FL1005215594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] Haitian People's Power Youth Organization [AJEPOPOA] leader Jude Leon Jean-Jacques is delighted with the Senate's decision to invest Justice Emile Jonassaint with presidential powers. This, he said, is a big step. [Begin Leon Jean-Jacques recording in Creole] The AJEPOPOA secretary general's office congratulates the Senate of the Republic for this important decision, following so many agreements, so many thoughts, and for its sense of responsibility for the higher interests of the nation by appointing Justice Emile Jonassaint as head of the state, considering the presidential vacuum under Article 149 of the Constitution. [end recording]
